    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe already have some LSP defaults:\n\n- \"grr\" is mapped in Normal mode to |vim.lsp.buf.references()|\n- \"grt\" is mapped in Normal mode to |vim.lsp.buf.type_definition()|\n...\n\nI want to create a map `CTRL-Wgrr`, run vim.lsp.buf.references() but it is expected to create a new tab page, then jumps to the target file if there is only 1 item. \n\nHow can we implement this? Should we add an option to `vim.lsp.ListOpts`?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nN/A",
